      • checkForOverlap

        public <T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>> boolean checkForOverlap​(T startTime1,
                                                                   T endTime1,
                                                                   T startTime2,
                                                                   T endTime2,
                                                                   boolean canBeAdjacent)
        Utility method for checking if two time periods overlap. Can check any Comparable time class. If times without dates are checked, the method assumes the same date. All Time parameters must be of the same type.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type of all time parameters. Must extend Comparable
        Parameters:
        startTime1 - The time object which represents the start time of time period 1. Can be any Comparable time object
        endTime1 - The time object which represents the end time of time period 1. Can be any Comparable time object
        startTime2 - The time object which represents the start time of time period 2. Can be any Comparable time object
        endTime2 - The time object which represents the end time of time period 2. Can be any Comparable time object
        canBeAdjacent - boolean value which determines whether or not a time period can end when another begins or begin when another ends. If true is passed in, method disregards times that start at the same time another ends, or end at the same time another begins.
        Returns:
        Returns true if an overlap is found, and false if there is no overlap found.
